# 2. FUNCTIONAL REQUIREMENTS DOCUMENT (FRD)
## Project: Hotel Booking Data Analysis System
## 2.1 System Overview
The system uses Excel/Python for data cleaning and Power BI for visualization of booking and cancellation insights.
## 2.2 Functional Requirements
•	F1: Analyze total bookings, cancellations, and customer segments.
•	F2: Show seasonality trends (month, week).
•	F3: Compare resort vs city hotels.
•	F4: Provide recommendations through insights.
## 2.3 Process Flow
1.	Import and clean data.
2.	Identify booking counts and categories.
3.	Analyze cancellation rates.
4.	Build KPI dashboards in Power BI.
## 2.4 Data Requirements
•	Booking status
•	Arrival date
•	Lead time
•	Hotel type
•	Customer type
•	Market segment
•	Duration of stay
## 2.5 User Interface Requirements
•	Monthly trend charts
•	Hotel comparison visuals
•	Cancellation rate KPIs
•	Filters for customer type and hotel type
## 2.6 Non-Functional Requirements
•	Dashboard should load within 30 seconds.
•	Should support multiple filters without performance issues.
# 3. User Stories
## User Story 1:
As a Hotel Manager, I want to see booking trends so I can plan resources.
Acceptance Criteria: Line chart of monthly bookings.
## User Story 2:
As a Revenue Manager, I want to analyze cancellation rates so I can reduce revenue loss.
Acceptance Criteria: Cancellation trend chart with filters.
________________________________________
# 4. Use Case Document
Use Case Name: Analyze Hotel Booking Data
Actor: Hotel Manager, BA
Trigger: Dashboard opens
## Main Flow:
1.	User opens dashboard
2.	Dashboard loads KPIs
3.	User applies filters
4.	Dashboard updates
5.	User reviews trends and insights
## Postcondition:
User understands booking behavior and cancellation patterns.

